Description:
update a metric table by adding a metric or heading

Usage: update_metric [-help]
                     [-format {html excel text}]
                     [-graph_type {treemap line none}] [-group <string>]
                     [-header <string>] [-link_file_metric <string>]
                     [-link_table <string>] [-metric <string>] [-no_shared_max]
                     [-renderer <string>] [-show_graph] -table <string>
                     [-title <string>]

-help                               # Prints out the command usage
-format {html excel text}           # config for specified report_metric format
                                    # (enum, optional)
-graph_type {treemap line none}     # type of graph to use in the table
                                    # (treemap|line|none) default is 'line'
                                    # (enum, optional)
-group <string>                     # group title to use in the html table
                                    # (string, optional)
-header <string>                    # header name to add (string, optional)
-link_file_metric <string>          # name of metric containing filename to
                                    # open when metric value is clicked
                                    # (string, optional)
-link_table <string>                # table to scroll to when the metric value
                                    # is clicked (string, optional)
-metric <string>                    # metric name to add (string, optional)
-no_shared_max                      # calculate Y axis maximum per row
                                    # (bool, optional)
-renderer <string>                  # force a specific html format renderer for
                                    # the metric (histogram) default is based
                                    # on metric type (string, optional)
-show_graph                         # whether to show this metric in a
                                    # comparison graph (bool, optional)
-table <string>                     # id of table to add metric to
                                    # (string, required)
-title <string>                     # title to use in the html table
                                    # (string, optional)